Their Arrow&#39;s Enrage<br />
<!--34-->Saruman&#39;s Reach x2  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Well if you couldn&#39;t tell off the bat it&#39;s another 70 card deck by Cat. I like that number it really works for me and I get to use all the cards that I think will work, or do work for me.<br />
<br />
Anyhow this is a Gandalf/Gimli deck designed to make the opponents Shadow weak, then run through and beat them up. It usually only moves 1 site at a time and the first site doesn&#39;t really matter to this deck. I prefere to go second with this deck.<br />
<br />
Your probably looking at it and wondering why those Allies are in the deck well, Elrond lets me draw some more cards usefull as always and Grimir allows me to get a Dwarven Event back into my deck, since Elrond heals himseld and Grimir they work together a nice little trick.<br />
<br />
As for the fellowship it&#39;s pretty straight forward as for the Shadow, well you want to make use of the Events for cancelling my opponents Archery and Enhancement events so that my Uruk-hai can make use of the Damage +1. One nice little trick that I did notice is that with Saruman&#39;s Reach/Uruk Spy combo - if you don&#39;t know what they do here they are:<br />
<br />
Saruman&#39;s Reach:<br />
Skirmish<br />
Manuever: Exert an Uruk-hai to make the opponent choose to either exert 2 companions or make the Ring-bearer put on The One Ring until the regroup phase.<br />
<br />
Uruk Spy:<br />
Response: If the Ring-bearer puts on The One Ring, exert this minion. Discard a card from the top of your draw deck for each (Uruk-hai symbol) minion you spot. Add a burden for each Shadow card discarded in this way.<br />
<br />
Well now lets say the opponent does indeed put on The One Ring and you have 3 Uruk&#39;s out there deck the top 3 and spot a couple of Shadow cards (not necessarily minions) and add some more Burdens. - In my honest opinon that&#39;s good... more burdens equals a more dead Ring Bearer and we all know how good that is.<br />
<br />
As for the rest it&#39;s pretty simple just look for the battles and make sure to make use of the Weather Events.<br />
<br />
Good Luck, <br />
Cat<br />
<br />
P.S. - Yes I know, 70 cards but read my other decks and you&#39;ll see that I like 70 card decks, they work for me and I make the best use of them. Also, when you rate, even if high, please offer any comments that might help the deck.<br />
<br />
Again thanks. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
